<TEXT>
temperatures fell the wind died down and the army arrived 
monday improving conditions for weary firefighters battling forest 
fires that have charred thousands of acres of montana and wyoming 
especially in yellowstone national park 
a first wave of 612 infantrymen from fort lewis wash landed 
at bozeman mont and headed for the 157000acre clover mist fire 
in yellowstones northeastern corner 
soldiers were to help prevent the fire one of 10 burning in the 
park involving about 350000 acres from crossing into montanas 
custer national forest or commercial areas of wyomings shoshone 
national forest 
park spokeswoman joan anzelmo said it was possible some of the 
soldiers might remain in the southern montana towns of cooke city 
and silvergate to help protect them from the clover mist fire 
burning about 3 miles to the south 
approximately 3000 firefighters were at work in yellowstone 
the nations first national park 
elsewhere reinforcements were called out in idaho to back up 
firefighters working to keep the 700acre eagle bar fire away from 
a timber sale tract in the payette national forest spokeswoman 
carla tipton said two 20member crews were on the scene and three 
more were expected an order was put in for 280 more people 
wind blew at only 5 to 15 mph monday in yellowstone down from 
saturdays 60 mph gusts 
however the parks south entrance remained closed forcing 
visitors coming from the south to detour about 150 miles to the 
parks west entrance at west yellowstone mont the northern gate 
and two eastern entries remained open 
other roads closed included the road from the south entrance to 
west thumb junction on the shore of yellowstone lake the road 
from madison junction to norris juction and on to indian creek and 
from norris to canyon junction an eastwest shortcut between the 
western and eastern sides of the main road that circles the park in 
a rough hourglass pattern 
the closings basically cut off the shortest route between the 
west and north entrances and closing the norriscanyon road meant 
the trip from madison junction on the western side of the park to 
the famous fishing bridge in the east went from 39 miles up to 54 
by way of the old faithful geyser the majority of the park 
remained accessible 
in addition the grant village area which contains a hotel 
campground visitor center and park staff dormitories was closed 
as were the norris pebble creek madison and lewis lake 
campgrounds the park contains 12 campgrounds 
south of yellowstone in grand teton national park and the 
bridgerteton national forest the hunter fire that had grown to 
more than 2900 acres in one day had calmed monday said don 
bright fire information officer 
in addition firefighters completed bulldozer lines around the 
southwest and northwest flanks of the hunter blaze and officials 
allowed residents evacuated saturday to return to their homes as 
well as guests of the teton science school and lost creek ranch 
bright said 
meanwhile a preliminary investigation concluded that a 
helicopter involved in firefighting efforts in the bighorn national 
forest crashed after it lost power to its rear rotor which 
stabilizes the craft investigators are unsure why the rotor lost 
power fire information officer harvalou buchanan said 
last fridays crash killed merrin rodgers 51 a bureau of land 
management communications technician and injured the pilot and two 
other passengers 
officials in montana took advantage of the calmer cooler 
weather to have crews dig a fire line by hand in rugged terrain 
along the southern edge of the 13dayold warm springs creek fire 
southeast of helena 
theyll be right at the burning edge fire information 
officer bob krepps said monday he said the 37200acre fire was 
only smoldering there monday allowing crews to go in with less 
risk 
officials predicted the fire would be contained tuesday night 
elsewhere in montana 20 smokejumpers parachuted into the storm 
creek fire that has burned 22000 acres of the absarokabeartooth 
wilderness and 80 more were to be taken in by fourwheel drive 
vehicles said beartooth district ranger phil jaquith the fire 
raced eight miles in a matter of hours saturday kicked up by high 
wind he said 
the hellroaring creek fire in a different section of the same 
giant wilderness area northeast of yellowstone national park had 
covered an estimated 24400 acres by monday spokeswoman maggie 
pittman said about 360 firefighters were working on the blaze 
which officials hope will burn into natural barriers 
in southeastern montana officials called for reinforcements to 
help battle a blaze out of control south of the northern cheyenne 
indian reservation don kendall of the department of state lands 
said the kirby fire fanned by wind blowing at 35 to 40 mph had 
grown to 10000 to 12000 acres but firefighters expected to 
contain the blaze tuesday 
