actress valerie harper denied from the 
witness stand monday that she demanded absolute control over the tv 
series she was fired from declaring i wasnt trying to be 
genghis khan 
i wanted to have participation early knowledge of stories so 
i would be in a partnership on the show she said of her 
situation comedy series valerie 
ms harper was called to the stand by attorneys for lorimar the 
production company suing her for alleged breach of contract she is 
countersuing the company contending it wrongfully fired her from 
the show 
attorney donald engel sought to show that ms harper was aware 
of all aspects of her 1985 contract with lorimar and tried to 
renegotiate it because she craved more money and total control over 
all aspects of the show 
ms harper denied this saying that she left business matters in 
the hands of her husband tony cacciotti and left the contract to 
her agent and lawyer whose advice she later came to doubt 
im not good with contracts she said holding the lorimar 
document i read these and start to get crosseyed 
ms harper acknowledged that even before the pilot for 
valerie was sold her relations with other members of the 
production staff began to erode 
the first problem she said arose when cacciottis name was 
left off the list of credits on the pilot for valerie even 
though he had acted as supervising producer 
i was disappointed and hurt she said it felt like a 
betrayal 
she told jurors that she and cacciotti have been business 
partners since 1979 and have been married just over a year 
engel enumerated the financial terms of the contract that 
brought ms harper 15 million for the first oneandahalf 
seasons on the air and provided profit shares and escalating 
salaries for her and her husband in subsequent years in the sixth 
season she would have received 90000 per episode 
didnt you realize that you had a very favorable deal asked 
engel 
i felt financially it was a start ms harper replied 
she faulted herself for letting too many unwritten agreements 
stay out of the contract 
there was a rush to sign the contract and they said well 
work out the details later she said 
ms harper said she sought to renegotiate her contract later to 
increase her salary and put in writing her creative participation 
in story ideas for each episode 
by then she conceded she felt she was losing the right to 
affect story lines 
the consultation i had enjoyed had eroded and the relationship 
with the producers had started to turn she said 
what you thought you had was total control said engel 
i would disagree said ms harper i wanted participation 
not controli wasnt trying to be genghis khan i wanted 
participation with people i loved and respected 
lorimar fired ms harper from the show a year ago and replaced 
her with sandy duncan the show is now known as the hogan 
family 
ms harpers testimony came on her 48th birthday but the event 
was not mentioned in the courtroom 
