<TEXT>
the agriculture departments 
businessandindustrial loan program has become a kingpin of the 
administrations rural development effort helping finance projects 
from catfish plants to macadamia nuts 
once despised by white house budget trimmers as something local 
communities and private citizens ought to do for themselves the 
bampi loans handled by the departments farmers home 
administration have enjoyed new status in recent years 
the financial battering of farmers in the early 1980s the 
hardships that hit the economy of smalltown america and the 
insistent demands of congress have helped jog the administration 
into a new look at rural development 
for the fiscal year that began last oct 1 according to fmha 
spokesman marlyn aycock bampi loan guarantees are expected to use 
the full 957 million authorized by congress the second year in a 
row that has happened 
according to fmha records the bampi volume soared to more than 1 
billion in 197980 before winding down under the reagan 
administration which unsuccessfully for several years advocated 
elimination of the program 
the usdas budget office in presenting proposals for fiscal 
1984 for example explained the reasons for seeking reduction or 
elimination of many of the fmha community programs including sewer 
and water assistance and bampi 
reductions in rural development program loans and grants 
reflect the administrations philosophy that private sector 
investment not public sector pump priming should drive 
development the usda said the federal role in the rural 
sector will be limited to that of lender of last resort in 
providing water sewer and community facilities essential to the 
health and safety of households where most needed in rural areas 
congress reduced annual authorizations for bampi in the early 
1980s and the administration kept the actual loan level far below 
that in 1984 for example when bampi was authorized at 200 
million the actual lending level was held to 124 million 
lending dropped to 61 million in 1985 and to 55 million in 
1986 then in 1987 when congress set the authority for bampi at 
957 million the full amount was used for the first time during 
the reagan administration 
aycock said that as of this april the bampi program had 2238 
loans outstanding for a total of 182 billion of those 475 
loans or 21 percent were delinquent a total of 230 million 
in its 16 years the bampi program has provided more than 7000 
guaranteed loans totaling nearly 6 billion according to the 
background information provided by fmha at the request of the 
associated press 
bampi was authorized by congress in 1972 to provide loans for 
the purpose of improving developing or financing business 
industry and employment and improving the economic and 
environmental climate in rural communities including pollution 
abatement and control 
an example of the programs intent was a 1974 loan to american 
cotton growers lubbock texas for 282 million to finance a new 
denim manufacturing plant in littlefield near the fields where 
cotton grew two more loans brought the total to 335 million 
jobs were created for more than 600 people and a ready market 
was provided for plains cotton the agency said it was made 
into highquality denim much of which was bought by levi strauss 
over the years the loan was paid in full on aug 4 1987 
some more recent examples include 
2 million for fishco inc belzoni miss to help build a 
catfish processing plant with a capacity of 40 million pound per 
year the plant is expected to employ 432 people when running at 
full capacity 
2 million for stoneville furniture company inc stoneville 
nc to buy equipment and machinery funds also will be used for 
working capital the plant employs approximately 700 
45 million for fairmont foods of minnesota inc fairmont 
minn to buy and reopen a food processing plant and to purchase 
new machinery and equipment to produce frozen processed foods the 
project will create 234 jobs 
the bampi loan program over the years also has been used for 
cotton gins the manufacture of radar guns used by police a 
shrimp farm in hawaii a chicken processing a radio station 
automobile dealerships and plants to make fuelgrade ethanol 
as another recent usda report described program operations 
ventures range from the processing and marketing of coffee beans 
and macadamia nuts in hawaii to the manufacturing of equipment to 
convert solid waste to boiler fuel in alaska 
under the recently enacted 39 billion droughtaid package the 
fmha was ordered to use bampi to the maximum extent possible to 
help businesses adversely affected by drought 
congress included 200 million for guaranteed loans to rural 
businesses and organizations to recover from drought losses those 
loans will have a lid of 500000 per individual 
</TEXT>
