the largest cocaine shipment ever seized in the united states 
in tampa fla on april 28 involved 9230 pounds found in plastic 
containers that were concealed in hallowedout lumber the largest 
in the new york city area occurred last month in hicksville where 
agents discovered 6000 pounds of cocaine hidden inside blocks of 
chocolate from ecuador 
only a few cocaine seizures nationally have exceeded 5000 
pounds but customs service agents in 10 months have seized 10 tons 
more cocaine than they did in all of the last fiscal year customs 
commissioner william von raab said earlier this month 
among those arrested this weekend was hernando grajales rizzo 
39 colombia a leader in the cali drug cartel stutman said 
stutman would not say when or how the smugglers brought the 
drugs into new york the drugs were found in the queens apartment 
where rizzo and two other men were arrested officials said 
the arrests were announced at a news conference where 
authorities displayed small plasticwrapped boxes containing the 
5000 pounds of cocaine and boxes of us currency 
some of the money was in supermarket bags imprinted with the 
reagan administrations slogan just say no to drugs 
the arrests would likely cause the cartel to suffer a setback 
but not end its activity in the lucrative new york market 
officials said 
i hope it will have an impact but the amount of the drugs 
coming in is very very large said chief raymond l jones of the 
city police departments organized crime control bureau the 
problem is that a 2pound 2ounce package a kilo can be broken 
down to about 14000 vials of crack that is our major problem 
the suspects will be arraigned this week authorities said 
