<TEXT>
pubs and bars throughout england and wales will be 
allowed to stay open through the afternoon starting today ending a 
73yearold policy and arousing some fears of increased drunkenness 
and violence 
pubs clubs and hotel bars may now stay open on weekdays from 11 
am to 11 pm instead of closing between 3 pm and 530 pm 
sunday afternoon hours have been extended by one hour from noon 
until 3 pm 
in 1915 the government decreed the afternoon closing to curb 
drinking by munitions workers parliament voted overwhelmingly in 
april to do away with the old rules 
but pubs do not have to change their hours if they do not want 
to and the national licensed victuallers association predicted 
that almost half the 67000 pubs in england and wales would stick 
to the old ways 
most backstreet and country pubs will probably continue to call 
time on weekdays at 3 pm 
the brewers society predicted at least 25000 new jobs would be 
generated by the longer drinking hours and that pubs would win back 
lost trade from hamburger and pizza bars 
pub owners and brewers agree that pubs in seaside and tourist 
towns and city bars will benefit most from increased trade 
home secretary douglas hurd said i believe that the new 
licensing hours will benefit society as a whole by giving people 
greater freedom of choice most people drink sensibly and 
responsibly and it makes no sense to deny them the opportunity to 
enjoy a drink in the afternoon at the time they wish 
the government has faced stiff opposition from the health lobby 
and critics who fear that drinkrelated crime particularly drunken 
violence by young rowdies and drunk driving will increase 
but champions of the new hours point out that extended hours in 
scotland introduced over a decade ago were followed by a reduced 
incidence of drunkenness and violence the scottish office said 
licensing changes had little impact on alcohol abuse 
in northern ireland most pubs increased alcohol sales during the 
past year in which pubs were allowed to open on sundays for the 
first time and open until later on weekdays 
but pub owners say there has been no increase in hooliganism and 
drunkenness northern ireland has had allday opening from monday 
to saturday since 1922 
the possible impact on the home has not been overlooked by the 
press the sunday mirror ran a tongueincheek story this week 
predicting that the extra drinking hour on sunday threatened to 
shake the fabric of british family life 
wives preparing sunday dinner can no longer even pretend to 
believe the man who tells you that hes just popping out to post a 
lettertake the dog for a walk 
