i understand further that when an officer ceases to be an mpd 
or other law enforcement officer this exempt status is not 
revoked and the former officer is not required to surrender the 
weapon 
the citys farreaching 1976 handgun ordinance which requires 
that all weapons purchased after that date be registered with the 
city should be amended to make clear that law enforcement officers 
are not exempt from this regulation cooke concluded 
police were telling people that once they left any police 
force they didnt have to register the weapon said raoul l 
carroll rowans attorney the memo makes that clear 
the document was included in material carroll submitted to 
district of columbia superior court in hopes of getting the charges 
dismissed 
beverly burke a spokeswoman for cooke said city officials 
still intend to prosecute the columnist she would not comment on 
the memo which she described as private not something that 
should be in the public domain police also declined to comment 
efforts to reach rowan for comment were not immediately 
successsful 
rowans trial has been set for sept 22 if convicted of 
possessing an unregistered weapon and ammunition he could receive 
