<TEXT>
gravediggers in northern burundi have 
counted the bodies of about 5000 people massacred in battles 
between members of the hutu and tutsi tribes government officials 
said monday 
government and un officials in neighboring rwanda said at 
least 35000 burundians crossed the border into rwanda to escape 
the slaughter last week 
in washington the state department said no americans were in the 
areas of the killings 
foreign minister cyprien mbonimpa of burundi included the first 
official death toll in an official communique issued at a morning 
briefing for diplomats 
it also was read during the 1 pm newscast on government radio 
according to diplomats who spoke in telephone interviews from 
bujumbura capital of the small densely populated country in 
central africa they asked that their names not be used 
it said the people in charge of burying the bodies have 
counted approximately 5000 a western diplomat said but whether 
that was the total dead was not unknown immediately 
it appeared as if they had concluded their work but it was 
not at all clear he said the facts are very very unclear and 
sketchy because of the remoteness of the area 
he said there appeared to have been no major violence since 
about 24 hours after the fighting began aug 14 between the hutu 
burundis majority tribe and the tutsi the minority tribe that 
controls the military and government 
members of the hutu and tutsi tribes are old enemies after a 
coup attempt in 1972 in the former belgium colony the tutsi 
massacred 100000300000 hutu including most of the tribes 
intelligentsia according to human rights groups 
the news didnt start coming down to bujumbura until late 
tuesday and wednesday the diplomat said the army went in on 
tuesday and got things under control fairly quickly 
mbonimpa the foreign minister described a media report that at 
least 24000 people were killed as highly exaggerated another 
diplomat said and from every report including those from 
nongovernmental sources no one believes that figure 
neighboring rwandas state radio said monday that 35000 people 
had crossed the border 
rwanda and burundi former belgian colonies are among the 
worlds most densely populated countries rwandan officials said 
resources were being strained by the influx of refugees 
in brussels the european economic community and belgium said 
they would send a planeload of tents blankets and other emergency 
aid for the refugees worth the equivalent of more than 700000 
according to rwandas official radio monitored in nairobi 
officials of the neighboring country met sunday at the border town 
of butare where the refugees were gathered it gave no details 
burundi claims last weeks violence was caused by expatriate 
hutus who infiltrated northern burundi from foreign countries and 
incited hutus to massacre tutsis 
the hutu people liberation party an exiled opposition group 
accused the tutsidominated military of massacring thousands of 
hutus but diplomatic sources said there was no evidence of that 
more than 90 percent of the population is hutu in the northern 
area around the marangara and ntega rural communes where most of 
last weeks killings occurred 
burundis communique said the government had the situation under 
control and the military the ruling union of national progress 
party and the bureaucracy had been ordered to show restraint 
one of the diplomats said 
it said the policy of the government was one of respect for 
human rights and of ethnic reconciliation he reported 
maj pierre buyoyas government has restricted travel between 
towns and is not allowing trips into the north the diplomats said 
a 7 pm to 5 am curfew is in force throughout the country and 
meetings of more than five people are prohibited 
the tribal battles were the first significant violence reported 
in burundi since buyoya seized power in a bloodless coup sept 3 
1987 while thenpresident jeanbaptiste bagaza was abroad 
nearly 5 million people live in burundi which is about the size 
of maryland its population is 84 percent hutu and 15 percent 
tutsi roughly the same tribal proportions apply in rwanda which 
is slightly smaller than burundi 
