<TEXT>
the aflcio said monday it will petition the 
reagan administration to restrict polish exports to us markets 
under provisions in the new trade bill that are designed to 
safeguard workers rights 
we certainly believe the worker rights provisions of the trade 
legislation should be applied in the case of poland said aflcio 
president lane kirkland they should be denied access to the 
american market under those provisions since they are in violation 
of worker rights 
kirkland made the comments on monday as the polish government 
ordered troops to secure major industrial plants and clamped 
curfews on three provinces hit by prosolidarity strikes following 
a week of the worst labor unrest since 1981 
the trade bill reagan is to sign tuesday in a ceremony before 
long beach calif dockworkers includes a provision permitting the 
us trade representative to retaliate against countries that deny 
worker rights such as recognition of free trade unions 
kirkland said he was told by the polish embassy here last week 
that his request for a visa to visit the country had been turned 
down for a third time 
the united states last year imported some 2615 million in 
products from poland primarily canned meat fish plates of iron 
steel nails clothing and glassware 
aflcio officials said the retaliation that the federation would 
seek from the reagan administration could take several forms 
including revoking polands mostfavorednation status as a trading 
partner 
the reagan administration revoked that status in 1981 upon the 
imposition of martial law in poland but gradually restored it with 
the aflcios approval after martial law was ended 
revocation of mostfavored status would raise the us tariffs 
on imports from poland for canned pork as an example the tariff 
would jump from a penny a pound to 325 cents a pound the tariff 
on cast iron pipes would jump from 8 percent to 25 percent 
also monday the aflcio elected new teamsters president william 
mccarthy as a vice president of the federation and to a seat on its 
policysetting executive council 
mccarthy fills the vacancy on the 35member board left by the 
death last month of his predecessor at the teamsters helm jackie 
presser 
