it is so heartbreaking another inmate says everyone in 
the visiting room starts crying it must be the most intense 
torture there is the intense pain of being emotionally helpless 
lizs daughters are growing into strangers she copes she says 
by not thinking about it 
you cant be a mother you try to be a friend says dora 
brown serving life for murder 
browns husband ran off with a younger woman and left her three 
sons to fend for themselves they lasted a month before they got 
into trouble and two were made wards of the state she has seen 
them twice in the past year 
sometimes there is sisterhood 
youll see it in people that you think my god theyre so 
violent theyre so cold theyre so everything all of a sudden 
this one woman is going to have a need and then the goofy one you 
think is so nuts responds gump says 
it is so good it is just so good you cant count on it but 
it manifests itself 
but mostly the women shut their turmoil inside if they didnt 
brown says it would be a mess around here 
easygoing as life is in alderson compared with other prisons 
temptation to escape remains charles manson disciple lynette 
squeaky fromme escaped last christmas when she thought her 
cult guru also in prison had cancer and i just had to get 
out she was captured after three days fromme was sentenced in 
an assassination attempt on thenpresident gerald ford 
