<TEXT>
in moon over parador paul mazursky reworks the prince and 
the pauper theme adds outrageous farce and produces a 
marvelously comic view of latin american politics and the acting 
profession 
mazurskys earlier career was marked by relationship 
comedydramas beginning with bob amp carol amp ted amp alice and 
continuing through next stop greenwich village an unmarried 
woman and willie and phil with down and out in beverly 
hills he broke through with a fullthrottle comedy moon over 
parador could repeat that success 
richard dreyfuss is a new york actor constantly on the prowl for 
that one starmaking role while he is playing a supporting role in 
a movie being shot on the caribbean island of parador he meets the 
dictatorpresident and does an imitation of him 
when the gourmand dictator dies of a heart attack during a 
carnival the chief of police and power behind the throne raul 
julia uncorks a daring idea dreyfuss could impersonate the late 
ruler and thus prevent a revolution under threat of death the 
actor accepts the role 
dreyfuss leaps into the impersonation performing a brilliant 
balcony speech before the populace but of course he cant deceive 
his servants who decide to go along with the scheme nor can he 
fool his mistress sonia braga who also agrees to keep his secret 
julia and his cohorts who appear to be left over from old nazi 
movies grow restless as dreyfuss begins to propose liberal 
reforms the natives are restless too and dreyfuss is nearly 
killed by bombs how he escapes from his predicament is an 
ingenious piece of scripting by mazursky and leon capetanos 
the success of moon over parador is due in large part to 
ideal casting dreyfuss brilliantly portrays the insecurities of a 
struggling actor and he proves a masterful farceur julia in a 
prussian wig is the embodiment of slick evil and braga is both 
funny and sexy 
mazursky highlights the comedy with reallife cameo appearances 
sammy davis jr sings for the carnival ike pappas plays a 
television reporter ed asner kids himself by paying a friendly 
visit to rebel camps in the mountains the only disappointment is 
the usually reliable jonathan winters his cia agent is written on 
the onenote venality that has become a movie cliche 
moon over parador is rated pg13 for bedroom scenes and 
language running time 104 minutes 
