<DOCNO> AP880822-0235 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
holly knight believes in the power of a good 
song 
if people like the artist but not the songs they wont buy 
the record said knight who has written the hits never for 
heart love touch for rod stewart and better be good to me 
for tina turner 
if you go to concerts you can see the reactions of people 
when they go into a song they like or know they sing and dance and 
go nuts as soon as they recognize the hit they stand up 
but after years of catapulting others to the limelight knight 
is seeking some recognition of her own she has just released her 
debut album holly knight and is counting on the strength of 
her writing to attract a following 
i liked the songs so much that when i handed the record over 
to the label i really didnt mind what song they picked for the 
single she said 
knight grew up in new york wanting to be a rock star more than a 
songwriter she began playing music at age 4 and was performing 
live as a teenager her talent as a songwriter emerged while she 
was a member of the groups spider and device 
my songs were starting to be the singles and get more 
attention when i left the group device i thought id write a 
song here or there and give them to people she said 
her first hit came in 1983 with love is a battlefield 
recorded by pat benatar knight does a softer version of the song 
on her own album 
i really like pattis version of it it gives people a chance 
to see how you can take the same song and make it sound really 
different she said 
knight is pleased with all the interpretations of her songs 
pointing out that the demos were similar to the finished product 
she singled out tina turner for you better be good to me 
i think the vocal delivery really suited her better be good 
to me suited her it suited her psychologically i think she did 
such a great job delivering it because she really meant it 
knight said 
her singing style is reminiscent of dusty springfield best 
known for such popsoul songs as son of a preacher man and i 
only want to be with you knight said she doesnt try to sound 
like any of her favorite singers but admires their approach 
daryl hall i was influenced by him aretha franklin a lot of 
my favorite singers are great but not technically brilliant 
knight coproduced her album with chris lordalge who has 
worked with bruce springsteen peter gabriel madonna and stevie 
nicks 
he lordalge was very encouraging she said i purely 
went on instinct with him everything he said was right along the 
lines of what i was thinking 
the album has a lush pop sound and little overdubbing was used 
its not 48 tracks knight said i did try to get three 
singers singing at once but i couldnt use any of it because it 
sounded too big it sounds rich because there isnt a lot of stuff 
on there so it gives room for whats on there to breathe 
still songwriting is what knight is known for and the songs on 
her album were worked on over a long period of time i may take 
months and months to write a song i might work on it and then 
leave it for a while and then go back to it 
knights writing is influenced by the motown and stax sounds of 
the 1960s 
i owned a supremes record before i owned a beatles record 
she said im doing some new songs now on one part i wanted to 
put horns on the horns sounded really out of tune they had that 
memphis sound lazy outoftune horns i was responding to those 
songs 
anyone hoping to turn an unrecorded knight song into a hit will 
be disappointed she is not prolific 
im not the kind of writer that writes 40 songs and a few 
become hits just about every song i write has become a hit 
knight said i dont put a lot out there in general people call 
me and want to know if i have a tune sitting around and i really 
dont 
knight wants to tour but will probably wait until next year 
she points out again how important it is for the audience to 
recognize the songs 
id like to have a couple of top 10s so people will know some 
of the music its going to be more exciting for them as well as me 
if people know the music 
its down to that again when you recognize a tune you dance 
and get into it it helps tide me over people are very comfortable 
with familiarity 
